before, and it looks a lot

00:21:02.496 --> 00:21:04.006 A:middle
better, because it -- the

00:21:04.166 --> 00:21:06.596 A:middle
centering is better than before,

00:21:07.336 --> 00:21:08.846 A:middle
and the size is more correct.

00:21:10.356 --> 00:21:11.626 A:middle
This will also be more

00:21:11.626 --> 00:21:12.296 A:middle
performance.

00:21:16.076 --> 00:21:17.806 A:middle
So if you do need a fixed size,

00:21:18.136 --> 00:21:19.256 A:middle
set the point size, but

00:21:19.256 --> 00:21:21.616 A:middle
otherwise have the symbol react

00:21:21.776 --> 00:21:23.606 A:middle
to the symbol configuration,

00:21:23.606 --> 00:21:25.336 A:middle
because even a large symbol

00:21:25.336 --> 00:21:26.616 A:middle
configuration or a small-scale

00:21:26.616 --> 00:21:27.756 A:middle
configuration may make a big

00:21:27.756 --> 00:21:29.446 A:middle
difference for the size of the

00:21:29.446 --> 00:21:30.096 A:middle
same symbol.

00:21:30.726 --> 00:21:35.456 A:middle
Now, there's a lot of

00:21:35.516 --> 00:21:38.426 A:middle
configurations here, and we've

00:21:38.426 --> 00:21:39.916 A:middle
established that symbols are --

00:21:39.916 --> 00:21:41.106 A:middle
Paolo mentioned before that

00:21:41.176 --> 00:21:42.646 A:middle
symbols are really made to work

00:21:42.646 --> 00:21:44.406 A:middle
with San Francisco, our system

00:21:44.436 --> 00:21:45.966 A:middle
font, but they work with any

00:21:45.966 --> 00:21:46.286 A:middle
font.

00:21:46.486 --> 00:21:48.646 A:middle
So you can use this API,

00:21:49.826 --> 00:21:51.406 A:middle
SymbolConfiguration(font, to

00:21:51.406 --> 00:21:52.526 A:middle
create a configuration that

00:21:52.586 --> 00:21:53.806 A:middle
matches the font you give it,

00:21:54.606 --> 00:21:56.056 A:middle
and it works with system fonts.

00:21:56.526 --> 00:21:58.396 A:middle
It works with dynamic type

00:21:58.396 --> 00:21:59.626 A:middle
fonts, but it also works with

00:21:59.626 --> 00:22:00.346 A:middle
custom fonts.

00:21:59.626 --> 00:22:00.346 A:middle
custom fonts.

00:22:00.686 --> 00:22:02.616 A:middle
And especially for custom fonts,

00:22:02.996 --> 00:22:04.046 A:middle
it will create a more

00:22:04.046 --> 00:22:06.716 A:middle
high-fidelity configuration than

00:22:06.716 --> 00:22:07.896 A:middle
the one you can create manually

00:22:07.896 --> 00:22:09.346 A:middle
by copying the values from the

00:22:09.346 --> 00:22:10.716 A:middle
font into your configuration.

00:22:11.446 --> 00:22:12.756 A:middle
So it's better to use this for

00:22:13.176 --> 00:22:13.926 A:middle
custom fonts.

00:22:14.326 --> 00:22:16.416 A:middle
And when you already have a

00:22:16.416 --> 00:22:17.796 A:middle
piece of text or a label that

00:22:17.796 --> 00:22:19.266 A:middle
has a font configured, this is

00:22:19.356 --> 00:22:20.246 A:middle
an easy way to create a

00:22:20.246 --> 00:22:21.736 A:middle
configuration that matches that

00:22:22.216 --> 00:22:22.726 A:middle
font.

00:22:26.766 --> 00:22:27.656 A:middle
And the last thing about

00:22:27.696 --> 00:22:29.386 A:middle
configurations is that they are

00:22:29.386 --> 00:22:29.896 A:middle
