00:37:22.726 --> 00:37:25.076 A:middle
But there's a few tips.

00:37:25.736 --> 00:37:28.416 A:middle
Prefer horizontal and vertical

00:37:28.466 --> 00:37:30.106 A:middle
centering over edge alignment.

00:37:30.786 --> 00:37:31.926 A:middle
It's a bit of a mental shift,

00:37:32.176 --> 00:37:33.906 A:middle
but once you figure it out, it

00:37:33.906 --> 00:37:34.606 A:middle
really works out.

00:37:36.016 --> 00:37:37.476 A:middle
And try to build your layouts

00:37:37.476 --> 00:37:40.316 A:middle
from the smallest element up to

00:37:40.316 --> 00:37:41.126 A:middle
the largest element.

00:37:41.126 --> 00:37:42.256 A:middle
It's pretty easy to start with

00:37:42.256 --> 00:37:43.866 A:middle
something small and then use it

00:37:43.866 --> 00:37:44.786 A:middle
as a building block to make

00:37:44.826 --> 00:37:45.476 A:middle
something larger.

00:37:45.556 --> 00:37:47.946 A:middle
And be flexible.

00:37:48.026 --> 00:37:49.576 A:middle
Image sizes can change.

00:37:50.396 --> 00:37:52.516 A:middle
Allow your image views to be the

00:37:52.516 --> 00:37:54.646 A:middle
size of their image but be aware

00:37:54.646 --> 00:37:55.486 A:middle
of the fact that they can

00:37:55.486 --> 00:37:55.946 A:middle
change.

00:37:56.526 --> 00:37:58.686 A:middle
It can be at run time, or it can

00:37:58.686 --> 00:38:01.606 A:middle
be over app launches, or even

00:37:58.686 --> 00:38:01.606 A:middle
be over app launches, or even

00:38:01.606 --> 00:38:02.966 A:middle
over system updates.

00:38:05.116 --> 00:38:06.946 A:middle
Caching images usually doesn't

00:38:06.946 --> 00:38:07.156 A:middle
help.

00:38:08.436 --> 00:38:09.816 A:middle
It's a great source of bugs, and

00:38:09.816 --> 00:38:11.306 A:middle
the system already does its best

00:38:11.356 --> 00:38:13.006 A:middle
to provide the best performance

00:38:13.166 --> 00:38:13.936 A:middle
that it can.

00:38:14.016 --> 00:38:16.186 A:middle
And caching really gives you an

00:38:16.186 --> 00:38:17.736 A:middle
override, so there's no need to

00:38:17.736 --> 00:38:18.086 A:middle
do that.

00:38:19.756 --> 00:38:22.026 A:middle
And finally, rasterizing is, in

00:38:22.026 --> 00:38:25.886 A:middle
most cases, the worst solution,

00:38:25.886 --> 00:38:27.586 A:middle
or the least-optimal solution to

00:38:27.586 --> 00:38:28.366 A:middle
fix the problem.

00:38:28.426 --> 00:38:32.386 A:middle
So save your CPU cycles for

00:38:32.386 --> 00:38:34.616 A:middle
something useful, and let the

00:38:34.616 --> 00:38:36.496 A:middle
system rasterize an image.

00:38:36.816 --> 00:38:38.316 A:middle
So try to avoid rasterizing

00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:40.486 A:middle
images, especially symbol

00:38:40.486 --> 00:38:40.946 A:middle
images.

